meta {
  name: Enroll factor
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{orgUrl}}/api/v1/authn/factors
  body: json
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "stateToken": "{{stateToken}}",
    "factorType": "sms",
    "provider": "OKTA",
    "profile": {
      "phoneNumber": "+15551234567"
    }
  }
}

script:post-response {
  if (res.status === 200 && res.body) {
    if (res.body.stateToken) bru.setVar('stateToken', res.body.stateToken);
    if (res.body._embedded && res.body._embedded.factor && res.body._embedded.factor.id) {
      bru.setVar('factorId', res.body._embedded.factor.id);
    }
  }
}

docs {
Enrolls a new MFA factor during an `MFA_ENROLL` transaction state.

**Common factor types:**
- `sms` — provider OKTA, profile.phoneNumber
- `call` — provider OKTA, profile.phoneNumber
- `push` — provider OKTA (Okta Verify Push)
- `token:software:totp` — provider OKTA or GOOGLE
- `email` — provider OKTA
- `webauthn` — provider FIDO

After enrollment, the factor is in PENDING_ACTIVATION until the user activates it (next request).

The new factor's ID is captured into `factorId`.
}
